<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="99">
All specimens were collected from patches of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Ranunculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ranunculus constantinopolitanus" order="Ranunculales" pageId="14" pageNumber="99" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="constantinopolitanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="99">Ranunculus constantinopolitanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Urv">d'Urv</normalizedToken>
. in damp places, often at woodland edges.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="99">
Adults are morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. consobrina" pageId="14" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="consobrina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="99">S. consobrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Klug, 1816), and most easily distinguished from that and other 
<taxonomicName authority="Stephens, 1835" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Sciapteryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sciapteryx" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="99">Sciapteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the pale parts of fore wing pterostigma, costa, and subcosta (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–53" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figures 48 - 53. Sciapteryx byzantina. 48, 49 female DEI-GISHym 31835 habitus; 50 head. 51 Male DEI-GISHym 31834 thorax; 52, 53 habitus." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.34309.figures48-53" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/310323" pageId="14" pageNumber="99">48</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–53" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figures 48 - 53. Sciapteryx byzantina. 48, 49 female DEI-GISHym 31835 habitus; 50 head. 51 Male DEI-GISHym 31834 thorax; 52, 53 habitus." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.34309.figures48-53" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/310323" pageId="14" pageNumber="99">49</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–53" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figures 48 - 53. Sciapteryx byzantina. 48, 49 female DEI-GISHym 31835 habitus; 50 head. 51 Male DEI-GISHym 31834 thorax; 52, 53 habitus." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.34309.figures48-53" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/310323" pageId="14" pageNumber="99">52</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–53" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figures 48 - 53. Sciapteryx byzantina. 48, 49 female DEI-GISHym 31835 habitus; 50 head. 51 Male DEI-GISHym 31834 thorax; 52, 53 habitus." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.34309.figures48-53" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/310323" pageId="14" pageNumber="99">53</figureCitation>
), as described in the key by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.9952" author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Entomology Series" pageId="17" pageNumber="102" pagination="111 - 207" refId="B4" refString="Benson, RB, 1968. Hymenoptera from Turkey, Symphyta. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Entomology Series 22 (4): 111 - 207, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.9952" title="Hymenoptera from Turkey, Symphyta. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.9952" volume="22" year="1968">Benson (1968)</bibRefCitation>
. The Bulgarian specimens agree well with the original description of this species (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.9952" author="Benson, RB" journalOrPublisher="Entomology Series" pageId="17" pageNumber="102" pagination="111 - 207" refId="B4" refString="Benson, RB, 1968. Hymenoptera from Turkey, Symphyta. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Entomology Series 22 (4): 111 - 207, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.9952" title="Hymenoptera from Turkey, Symphyta. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.9952" volume="22" year="1968">Benson 1968</bibRefCitation>
), except for the following details: body length is 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8-9 mm</quantity>
(as given also by Benson), but one male only 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" unit="mm" value="7.0">7mm</quantity>
; labial and maxillary palps largely pale, but apical palpomeres more or less dark (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–53" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figures 48 - 53. Sciapteryx byzantina. 48, 49 female DEI-GISHym 31835 habitus; 50 head. 51 Male DEI-GISHym 31834 thorax; 52, 53 habitus." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.34309.figures48-53" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/310323" pageId="14" pageNumber="99">50</figureCitation>
) (Benson wrote only that the labial palps are yellowish white); distal margin of tergum 1 more or less pale, but entirely black in one female (Benson wrote that apical margins of all terga are more or less pale); outer margin of tegula more or less pale, and inside dark (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–53" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figures 48 - 53. Sciapteryx byzantina. 48, 49 female DEI-GISHym 31835 habitus; 50 head. 51 Male DEI-GISHym 31834 thorax; 52, 53 habitus." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.34309.figures48-53" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/310323" pageId="14" pageNumber="99">51</figureCitation>
) (Benson wrote that the &quot;front half of tegula&quot; is pale).
</paragraph>
