<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="100">
<pageBreakToken pageId="15" pageNumber="100" start="start">The</pageBreakToken>
COI barcode region of DEI-GISHym88746 shows a divergence of 5.3% from the closest neighbour, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stephens, 1835" authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Sciapteryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sciapteryx laeta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laeta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="100">Sciapteryx laeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Konow, 1891 (DEI-GISHym4857).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="100">
The host plants of most 
<taxonomicName authority="Stephens, 1835" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Sciapteryx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sciapteryx" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="100">Sciapteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species remain unrecorded, but because at least 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. costalis" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="costalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="100">S. costalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. consobrina" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="consobrina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="100">S. consobrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known to use 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Ranunculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ranunculus" order="Ranunculales" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="100">Ranunculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species as hosts (
<bibRefCitation author="Lorenz, H" journalOrPublisher="Abhandlungen zur Larvalsystematik der Insekten" pageId="18" pageNumber="103" pagination="1 - 389" refId="B41" refString="Lorenz, H, Kraus, M, 1957. Die Larvalsystematik der Blattwespen (Tenthredinoidea und Megalodontoidea). Abhandlungen zur Larvalsystematik der Insekten 1: 1 - 389" title="Die Larvalsystematik der Blattwespen (Tenthredinoidea und Megalodontoidea)." volume="1" year="1957">Lorenz and Kraus 1957</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Benes, K" journalOrPublisher="Acta Universitatis Carolinae, Biologica" pageId="17" pageNumber="102" pagination="193 - 198" refId="B2" refString="Benes, K, 1960. Beitrag zur Bionomie und Morphologie der Larven von Sciapteryx consobrina (Kl.) (Hymenoptera: Tenthredinidae). Acta Universitatis Carolinae, Biologica 60 (3): 193 - 198" title="Beitrag zur Bionomie und Morphologie der Larven von Sciapteryx consobrina (Kl.) (Hymenoptera: Tenthredinidae)." volume="60" year="1960">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Beneš">Benes</normalizedToken>
1960
</bibRefCitation>
), we speculate that 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. constantinopolitanus" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="constantinopolitanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="100">R. constantinopolitanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the larval host of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. byzantina" pageId="15" pageNumber="100" rank="species" species="byzantina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="100">S. byzantina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
